Systems Administrator & Hacker - 17C - ACASP - US Army

United States Army

- Plattsburgh, NY 12901

===================== > > > > > READ THE NOTES! =======================
NOTE 1: Acceptance of this position requires ENLISTMENT in the U.S. Army (active duty).
NOTE 2: If you are farther than 75 miles from this office, you should consider going to your local Army Recruiting Office.
NOTE 3: There are 2 versions of this job. This listing is for the non-entry level position that requires previous experience or certifications. The other is an entry level version that is open to all who apply.
==============================================================================
Already a Sys-Admin? Wanna be a HACKER? Legally.....for the ARMY!
Army Civilian Acquired Skills Program (ACASP)
If you’re already a Systems Administrator and meet the listed requirements you can enlist in the Army under the ACASP program for 17C Cyber Operations Specialist. You’ll do basic training and then skip job training because you're already certified in the job the Army needs you for. Because of already having the skills the Army needs you'll also enlist at a higher rank, as a "Specialist" (Pay grade E4). This is 3 ranks higher than standard entry level "Private" (Pay grade E1).
REQUIREMENTS FOR 17C ACASP:
Must fulfill one of the following options:
(1) Possess a Bachelor’s Degree in:
Computer Science
Information Technology Management
Cyber Security
Cyber Forensics
Similar cyber-related degree program from an accredited college or university (cyber policy degree does not qualify for this program)
(2) Have a combination of at least four years of both formal education (in study areas previously indicated) and work experience with government or industry in
Computer Science
Information Technology Management
Cyber Security
or Cyber Forensics fields, including software development, penetration testing, cyber incident response, and cyber related encryption/decryption;
(3) Have at least four years work experience with government or industry in
Computer Science
Information Technology Management
Cyber Security
or Cyber Forensics fields, including software development, penetration testing, cyber incident response, and cyber-related encryption/decryption, and possess current professional certifications in Certified Ethical Hacker (CEH), Network+, and Security+.
Additionally, possession of professional certifications in one or more of the following is considered favorably for participation in this program:
A+
Certified Information Systems auditor (CISA)
Certified Information Security Manager (CISM)
Certified Information Systems Security Professional (CISSP)
Global Information Assurance Certification (GIAC).
SALARY
Pay is salary by rank, not hourly. $31,608 annual starting pay. You pay has 3 parts: rank pay, food money, rent money.
Rank Pay: for a Specialist (paygrade E4) is $27,144 annual
Food Money: $4,464 annual
Rent Money: depends on where you live (barracks, base housing, off-base) but is added on top of your rank and food pays.
If you want a further explanation of this, ask a recruiter or someone you know who has been on active duty in the military.
PTO & Vacation:
30 days vacation per year (you're salary, so it's paid)
Most federal holidays are also days off for the Army.
INSURANCE
Tricare Prime – Full healthcare coverage for you and your dependents at no cost to you.
EDUCATION BENEFITS
Post 9/11 GI Bill for college, 100% tuition coverage at any state funded school, plus rent money while in school.
Tuition Assistance Program (TAP), $4,000 per year for college (separate fund, not part of GI Bill)
